==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Seriema
<hw>Ser`i*e"ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Native
name.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>either of two large South American
birds related to the cranes, the <altname>cariama</altname> of Southern
Brazil (<spn>Cariama cristata</spn>, formerly <spn>Dicholophus
cristata</spn>) or the <spn>Chunga burmeisteri</spn> of Argentina. They
have an erectile crest and a short, broad bill. They are often
domesticated.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

